member.name: T:TI.ZPI2.APP_MSG_RSP.BLIND_NODE_RESPONSE
TI.ZPI2.APP_MSG_RSP.BLIND_NODE_RESPONSE
member.summary: This message is sent out of the Blind Node in response to the "Bind Node Request" message. The blind node, upon receiving the request message, will send a "Reference Node Request" (radius 1 - broadcast) to its immediate neighbors and wait for responses. Use the Blind Node Configuration message to change the parameters used to generate this response message (ie. number of reference node response, collect time)
